{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "The paraffin sections were deparaffined with the following procedure: 2 × 5 min Xylene, 2 × 5 min 100% Ethanol, 2 × 5 min 95% Ethanol, and 5 min 70% Ethanol.",
    "The sections (cryosections or deparaffined sections) were rehydrated in ddH 2 O for 5 min, stained in Hematoxylin for 1.5 min, and rinsed for 5 min under running tape water.",
    "0.1% Eosin was applied for 1.5 min, washed by dipping in water, and differentiated in 70% Ethanol for 3 min.",
    "Dehydration was done with the following changing of buffers: 3 min 85% Ethanol, 2 × 5 min 100% Ethanol, 2 × 5 min Xylene.",
    "The sections were mounted with Eukitt and imaged with Axioscan (Zeiss) or Tissue FAXS Plus (Tissue Gnostics, California, USA)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}